ndary); } Using Tool | Deep Thinking Total: 7 Tasks 5 Tasks Remaining Create main index.html with navigation, dashboard, and chapter overview Create CSS styling with aviation theme Create JavaScript for interactivity, progress tracking, quiz engine Build chapter content pages with summaries, key terms, memory aids Build interactive quiz/review questions for each major topic Create quick-reference cards and study tools Update README.md with project documentation Now let me build the comprehensive data file with all chapter content: Using Tool | Write File js/data.js // ============================================================ // PHAK STUDY HUB — DATA FILE // FAA Pilot's Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge FAA-H-8083-25C ... { term: \"VSI\", def: \"Vertical Speed Indicator. Shows climb/descent rate in FPM. Has ~6-9 sec lag.\", chapter: \"Ch. 8\" }... { term: \"Vx\", def: \"Best angle of climb. Max altitude per distance. For obstacle clearance.\", chapter: \"Ch. 9\" }, { term: \"Vy\", def: \"Best rate of climb. Max altitude per time. Used for normal climb.\", chapter: \"Ch. 9\" } ]; Now let me build the main app JavaScript: Using Tool | Write File js/app.js // ============================================================ // PHAK STUDY HUB — APP.JS // Interactive Knowledge Base Application Logic ... closeQuiz(); closeGlossary(); } }); Using Tool | Deep Thinking Total: 5 Tasks 1 Task Remaining Create JavaScript for interactivity, progress tracking, quiz engine Build chapter content pages with summaries, key terms, memory aids Build interactive quiz/review questions for each major topic Create quick-reference cards and study tools Update README.md with project documentation Using Tool | Write File README.md # ✈️ FAA PHAK Study Hub ### Interactive Knowledge Base — Private Pilot Written Exam Prep ... --- *Created for FAA Written Exam study prep. All content based on FAA-H-8083-25C. Always verify with current official FAA p... Using Tool | Deep Thinking Total: 1 Task 0 Tasks Remaining Update README.md with project documentation Now let me test it: Using Tool | Playwright Console Capture Clean — zero errors. Let me do a quick visual check to verify the content renders: Using Tool | Playwright Console Capture Zero errors. Let me verify the file structure looks right: Using Tool | List Directory List directory Using Tool | List Directory js/ Everything is built and clean. Here's your complete FAA PHAK Study Hub — here's exactly what you got: ✈️ Your FAA PHAK Study Hub Is Live 🎯 What Was Built A full interactive knowledge base for the FAA Private Pilot Written Exam, covering all 17 chapters of the official FAA-H-8083-25C handbook. 📚 Feature Breakdown Feature\tDetails 17 Chapter Summaries\tComprehensive exam-focused notes for every PHAK chapter 62+ Practice Questions\tPer-chapter quizzes with instant answers + explanations Quick Quiz Mode\tRandom 10-question cross-chapter drill (simulates FAA exam pressure) Key Terms (expandable)\t150+ definitions organized per chapter Memory Aids / Mnemonics\tARROW, IMSAFE, TVMDC, DECIDE, PAST, HHSH, 3-152, 5-111, and more Progress Tracking\tSaved in browser — persists between sessions Quick Reference Tables\t6 tabs: Airspace, Weather, Regulations, Performance, Instruments, All Mnemonics Searchable Glossary\t50+ aviation terms with chapter citations FAA Source Links\tEvery chapter links back to the official PHAK PDF 🔥 Highest-Priority Exam Topics Covered Airspace (~20% of exam) — Full class table, VFR minimums, special use airspace Weather (~15%) — Fog types, thunderstorms, stability, cloud types Aerodynamics (~13%) — Four forces, stall, load factor, angle of attack Navigation (~12%) — TVMDC, VOR, sectional charts, dead reckoning Weight & Balance (~10%) — Full calculation method, CG effects, standard weights 🚀 To Deploy Go to the Publish tab and click publish — your study portal will be live at a shareable URL. Perfect for studying on any device, anywhere. FAA Pilot Handbook Study Knowledge Base Task completed: AI Developer View Result Agent at Work | AI Docs FAA Written Exam Master Knowledge Base View Using Tool | Summarize Large Document Provide the official table of contents and chapter list for FAA-H-8083-25C Pilot’s Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge. Return chapter numbers, exact chapter titles, and a 1-2 sentence summary of what each chapter covers. Also identify appendices, glossary, and index. Using Tool | Summarize Large Document For FAA-H-8083-25C, summarize Chapters 1 through 4 for a student preparing for the FAA written exam. For each chapter, give: core ideas, high-yield exam topics, must-know definitions/formulas if any, and common student mistakes. Using Tool | Summarize Large Document For FAA-H-8083-25C, summarize Chapters 5 through 8 for a student preparing for the FAA written exam. For each chapter, give: core ideas, high-yield exam topics, must-know definitions/formulas if any, and common student mistakes. Using Tool | Summarize Large Document For FAA-H-8083-25C, summarize Chapters 9 through 12 for a student preparing for the FAA written exam. For each chapter, give: core ideas, high-yield exam topics, must-know definitions/formulas if any, and common student mistakes. Using Tool | Summarize Large Document For FAA-H-8083-25C, summarize Chapters 13 through 17 plus appendices/glossary for a student preparing for the FAA written exam. For each chapter, give: core ideas, high-yield exam topics, must-know definitions/formulas if any, and common student mistakes. Using Tool | Summarize Large Document From FAA-H-8083-25C, extract a study roadmap for passing the FAA written exam using this handbook: recommended study sequence, which chapters are most foundational, which chapters are calculation-heavy, which chapters are memory-heavy, and a concise glossary of the most testable terms a student should memorize first. Using Tool | Doc Generate Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a polished, interactive HTML knowledge base for studying the FAA written exam based on the official FAA Pilot’s Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge, FAA-H-8083-25C. Use a clean aviation-inspired design with blue/white/gray palette, sticky top navigation, responsive layout, anchor links, collapsible chapter sections using <details>, a search/filter box for chapter cards, and small JS interactions for filtering and saving checkbox progress in localStorage. Document title: FAA Written Exam Study Knowledge Base Subtitle: Master Study Guide Based on FAA-H-8083-25C Pilot’s Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge Use this format because it should feel like an interactive study dashboard, not a plain article. Required top section: - Prominent title and subtitle - A short summary explaining this is a study knowledge base built from the official FAA handbook for written exam prep - Official source link to: https://www.faa.gov/regulations_policies/handbooks_manuals/aviation/faa-h-8083-25c.pdf - A source integrity note: “This knowledge base is derived from the official FAA handbook linked above. Always cross-check with current FAA regulations, the applicable Airman Certification Standards (ACS), FAR/AIM, and FAA test supplement materials.” Create these main sections in this order: 1) Executive Overview 2) How to Use This Knowledge Base 3) Study Roadmap 4) High-Yield Exam Topics by Chapter 5) Key Definitions and Formulas 6) FAA Written Exam Cram Sheet 7) Resource and Fact-Check Log 8) Knowledge Base Update Notes Section requirements: 1) Executive Overview - Brief explanation of what the handbook covers - State the 17 chapter titles exactly: 1. Introduction To Flying 2. Aeronautical Decision-Making 3. Aircraft Construction 4. Principles of Flight 5. Aerodynamics of Flight 6. Flight Controls 7. Aircraft Systems 8. Flight Instruments 9. Flight Manuals and Other Documents 10. Weight and Balance 11. Aircraft Performance 12. Weather Theory 13. Aviation Weather Services 14. Airport Operations 15. Airspace 16. Navigation 17. Aeromedical Factors - Mention Appendix A, B, C, Glossary, and Index 2) How to Use This Knowledge Base - Create a tactical SOP table with columns: Phase | What You Study | Expected Input | Expected Output | Why It Matters - Use 5 rows: Foundation, Weather/Environment, Systems/Instruments, Math/Performance/Navigation, Human Factors/Final Review - Make it practical for a nontechnical learner 3) Study Roadmap - Include a visual process flow using styled cards/arrows for 4 phases: Phase 1 Basics: Chapters 1,3,4,5,6 Phase 2 Environment: Chapters 12,13,14,15 Phase 3 Technical + Math: Chapters 7,8,10,11,16 Phase 4 Human Factors + Final Review: Chapters 2,17,9 + Appendices - Add a roadmap table with columns: Week/Block | Chapters | Focus | Expected Input | Expected Output | Evidence/Rationale - Fill with at least 6 study blocks - Evidence/rationale should mention why foundational chapters come first, which are calculation-heavy, and which are memory-heavy 4) High-Yield Exam Topics by Chapter - Create one collapsible <details> card for each of the 17 chapters - Each chapter card must contain: - One-sentence chapter summary - Bullet list: Core ideas - Bullet list: High-yield exam topics - Bullet list: Must-know definitions/formulas if applicable - Bullet list: Common student mistakes - A “Study Output” callout that states what the learner should be able to do after studying that chapter - Use the following factual content as the basis, written in polished language without inventing unsupported details: Chapters 1-4: * Chapter 1: FAA role, 14 CFR, pilot certification path, category/class/type distinctions; common confusion between airman category and aircraft category. * Chapter 2: ADM, human factors, hazardous attitudes and antidotes, PAVE, IMSAFE, DECIDE, SRM. * Chapter 3: Major aircraft components, truss/monocoque/semimonocoque, composites, CG and stability basics. * Chapter 4: Standard atmosphere, Bernoulli/Newton concepts, pressure altitude vs density altitude, temp/pressure/humidity effects. Chapters 5-8: * Chapter 5: Four forces, stability, stalls caused by critical angle of attack, left-turning tendencies, load factor, ground effect, wake turbulence. * Chapter 6: Primary/secondary controls, axes of rotation, adverse yaw, trim, flaps, T-tail deep stall concept. * Chapter 7: Reciprocating engines, carburetor ice, carb heat effects, detonation vs preignition, fuel grades, magnetos, FADEC. * Chapter 8: Pitot-static system, gyros, altimeter and airspeed concepts, variation vs deviation, compass errors, “high to low, look out below.” Chapters 9-12: * Chapter 9: AFM vs POH, ARROW documents, airworthiness, inspections, preventative maintenance, inoperative equipment under 91.213(d), ADs. * Chapter 10: Weight x Arm = Moment, Total Moment / Total Weight = CG, effects of forward vs aft CG, fuel weight at 6 lb/gal. * Chapter 11: Density altitude, performance charts, interpolation, Vx vs Vy, wind effects, ground effect. * Chapter 12: Atmospheric heating, stability, clouds, fog, fronts, thunderstorms, dew point relationships, cloud base estimation. Chapters 13-17: * Chapter 13: METAR, SPECI, TAF, PIREP, SIGMET, AIRMET, NEXRAD delay issues, Zulu time. * Chapter 14: Runway markings/signs/lights, runway incursions, LAHSO, CTAF, light gun signals, wake turbulence avoidance. * Chapter 15: Regulatory vs nonregulatory airspace, Class A-G basics, VFR weather minimums, Class B/C/D entry requirements, TFRs, special use airspace. * Chapter 16: Pilotage, dead reckoning, VOR, GPS, RAIM, variation/deviation, wind correction, time/speed/distance/fuel formulas. * Chapter 17: Hypoxia types, hyperventilation, spatial disorientation, alcohol/drug rules, fatigue, diving after flying. 5) Key Definitions and Formulas - Create two side-by-side panels: A) Most Testable Definitions (at least 18 items) including Angle of Attack, Density Altitude, Pressure Altitude, Category, Class, Type, Moment, Arm, Datum, Load Factor, Variation, Deviation, METAR, TAF, CTAF, Hypoxia, Stall, Vx, Vy B) Must-Know Formulas / Conversions including: Weight × Arm = Moment Total Moment ÷ Total Weight = CG Time = Distance ÷ Groundspeed Fuel Used = Time × Burn Rate Standard atmosphere: 29.92 in Hg and 15°C at sea level Standard lapse rate: about 2°C per 1,000 ft Pressure lapse rate: about 1 in Hg per 1,000 ft Fuel weight avgas ≈ 6 lb/gal Density altitude = pressure altitude corrected for nonstandard temperature Cloud base estimate AGL ≈ ((Temp − Dew Point) / 4.4) × 1,000 - Add a warning note that performance calculations must be verified against the aircraft POH/AFM and FAA test materials 6) FAA Written Exam Cram Sheet - Create a compact priority matrix table with columns: Topic Cluster | Priority | What to Memorize | What to Practice | Expected Exam Output - Include at least these clusters: Airspace, Weather Reports/Forecasts, Weight and Balance, Performance, Navigation, Aerodynamics/Stalls, Instruments, Airport Ops, ADM/Aeromedical 7) Resource and Fact-Check Log - Create a table with columns: Source | Type | What It Supports | URL - Include at minimum: FAA-H-8083-25C official PDF FAA Pilot’s Handbook landing page: https://www.faa.gov/regulations_policies/handbooks_manuals/aviation/phak - Add a brief note that this study KB is intentionally based on official FAA materials only in this version 8) Knowledge Base Update Notes - Add a boxed section labeled “Knowledge Base Master Record — Chat Thread 01” - Include bullets for: Master document created Current scope: FAA PHAK written exam study base Next logical expansion pages: flashcards, chapter quizzes, mnemonic sheet, practice schedule, wrong-answer log, oral exam bridge notes Status: Version 1 initialized Other design/content requirements: - Add a mini table of contents near the top linking to all major sections - Add “Back to top” links after each major section - Use badges/tags like Foundational, Calculation-Heavy, Memory-Heavy, Safety-Critical - Include a small legend explaining those tags - Include a note that this is a study guide, not a substitute for flight instruction - Keep tone tactical, clear, and exam-focused - Do not mention politics or unrelated current events - Use only information supported by the official FAA handbook summary provided above; do not add unverified claims - Make the final HTML elegant, complete, and ready for study immediately. Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 183,420 Using Tool | Doc Grep Search: id=\"top\"|href=\"#top\" Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 1096,1135 Using Tool | Doc Edit --- a/document.html+++ b/document.html@@ -47,10 +47,40 @@         text-decoration: underline; } .nav-toc { -        background-color: #f7fafc; +        background-color: rgba(247, 250, 252, 0.96); border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 30px; +        position: sticky; +        top: 0; +        z-index: 20; +        backdrop-filter: blur(6px); +        box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(26, 54, 93, 0.08); +      } +      .flow-grid { +        display: grid; +        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); +        gap: 12px; +        align-items: stretch; +        margin-bottom: 20px; +      } +      .flow-card { +        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fbff 0%, #edf2f7 100%); +        border: 1px solid #cbd5e0; +        border-radius: 10px; +        padding: 14px; +        font-family: Arial, sans-serif; +        box-shadow: 0 8px 18px rgba(43, 108, 176, 0.08); +      } +      .flow-arrow { +        text-align: center; +        font-size: 1.4em; +        color: #2b6cb0; +        margin: 4px 0 10px; +        font-family: Arial, sans-serif; +      } +      .badge-row { +        margin-top: 8px; } .nav-toc ul { list-style-type: none; @@ -180,7 +210,7 @@       } </style> </head> -  <body> +  <body id=\"top\"> <h1>FAA Written Exam Study Knowledge Base</h1> <h3>Master Study Guide Based on FAA-H-8083-25C Pilot’s Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge</h3> @@ -305,12 +335,40 @@ <!-- SECTION 3 --> <h2 id=\"sec3\">3) Study Roadmap</h2> -    <div style=\"background: